MARY: No!

34
00:02:40.110 --> 00:02:42.121
Mary?

35
00:02:42.145 --> 00:02:43.145
Mary!

36
00:02:45.449 --> 00:02:46.449
Mary.

37
00:02:47.484 --> 00:02:49.562
Mary.

38
00:02:49.586 --> 00:02:51.085
[SAM GURGLING]

39
00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:57.943
Hey. Sammy.

40
00:02:59.112 --> 00:03:00.912
You okay?

41
00:03:17.164 --> 00:03:18.796
No! Mary!

42
00:03:26.207 --> 00:03:28.506
[WAILING]

43
00:03:31.745 --> 00:03:33.590
DEAN: Daddy!

44
00:03:33.614 --> 00:03:34.724
Take your brother outside

45
00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:36.226
as fast as you can.
Don't look back.

46
00:03:36.250 --> 00:03:37.482
Now. Dean. Go!

47
00:03:41.055 --> 00:03:43.037
Mary!

48
00:03:43.891 --> 00:03:45.357
No!

49
00:03:53.767 --> 00:03:55.133
It's okay. Sammy.

50
00:03:57.638 --> 00:03:58.737
I got ya.

51
00:04:03.643 --> 00:04:05.793
[SIRENS WAILING]

52
00:04:07.514 --> 00:04:09.648
It's all right. I got
it. Move the line up.

53
00:04:11.918 --> 00:04:12.918
Here.

54
00:04:14.288 --> 00:04:16.600
MAN [OVER
RADIO]: <i>Uh. dispatch...</i>

55
00:04:16.624 --> 00:04:18.304
MAN: Stand back. sir!

56
00:04:26.100 --> 00:04:27.877
MAN: Let's get a
stream on the right side.

57
00:04:27.901 --> 00:04:30.780
Hey. just stay back.
You have to stay back.

58
00:04:30.804 --> 00:04:33.037
Come on. You have
to stay on the curb.

59
00:04:42.583 --> 00:04:46.930
[THE LIVING DAYLIGHTS'
"GASOLINE" PLAYING]

60
00:04:46.954 --> 00:04:49.482
Sam. Get a move on. would ya?

61
00:04:49.506 --> 00:04:52.618
We're supposed to be
there. like. 15 minutes ago.

62
00:04:52.642 --> 00:04:54.954
Sam. You comin' or what?

63
00:04:54.978 --> 00:04:55.955
Do I have to?

64
00:04:55.979 --> 00:04:57.106
Yes.

65
00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:58.741
It'll be fun.

66
00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:01.098
And where is your costume?

67
00:05:02.168 --> 00:05:04.146
[SNICKERS]

68
00:05:04.170 --> 00:05:06.800
You know how I
feel about Halloween.

69
00:05:06.824 --> 00:05:08.468
[HIP-HOP MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKER]

70
00:05:08.492 --> 00:05:10.653
<i>♪ Shorty. what you gonna
do Yeah. what you gonna do ♪</i>

71
00:05:10.677 --> 00:05:13.022
<i>♪ Are you gonna get in
Yeah. what you gonna do... ♪</i>

72
00:05:13.046 --> 00:05:15.758
So here's to Sam and
his awesome LSAT victory.

73
00:05:15.782 --> 00:05:17.726
All right. all right.
It's not that big a deal.

74
00:05:17.750 --> 00:05:20.229
He acts all humble.
but he scored a 174.

75
00:05:20.253 --> 00:05:21.264
Mmm.

76
00:05:21.288 --> 00:05:22.265
Is that good?

77
00:05:22.289 --> 00:05:23.666
Scary good. [LAUGHS]

78
00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:26.102
So there you go. You
are a first-round draft pick.

79
00:05:26.126 --> 00:05:28.237
You can go to any
law school you want.

80
00:05:28.261 --> 00:05:31.007
Actually. I got an
interview here. Monday.

81
00:05:31.031 --> 00:05:32.875
If it goes okay. I
think I got a shot

82
00:05:32.899 --> 00:05:34.243
at a full ride next year.

83
00:05:34.267 --> 00:05:36.512
Hey. It's gonna go great.

84
00:05:36.536 --> 00:05:38.348
It better.

85
00:05:38.372 --> 00:05:40.749
How does it feel to be the
golden boy of your family?

86
00:05:40.773 --> 00:05:42.151
Ah. they don't know.

87
00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:43.619
Don't know? I would be gloating.

88
00:05:43.643 --> 00:05:44.787
Why not?

89
00:05:44.811 --> 00:05:47.256
'Cause we're not
exactly the Bradys.

90
00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.258
And I'm not exactly the
Huxtables. More shots.

91
00:05:49.282 --> 00:05:50.259
No. No.

92
00:05:50.283 --> 00:05:51.260
No.

93
00:05:51.284 --> 00:05:52.428
Hey. seriously.

94
00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:53.696
I'm proud of you.

95
00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:55.098
You'll knock 'em dead on Monday.

96
00:05:55.122 --> 00:05:56.732
and you're gonna
get that full ride.

97
00:05:56.756 --> 00:05:57.955
I know it.

98
00:05:58.825 --> 00:06:00.436
What would I do without you?

99
00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:02.305
Crash and burn.

100
00:06:02.329 --> 00:06:03.406
<i>♪ What you gonna do. punk? ♪</i>

101
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:04.607
<i>♪ Are you gonna get in? ♪</i>

102
00:06:04.631 --> 00:06:06.342
<i>♪ Yeah. what you gonna do? ♪</i>

103
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:09.379
<i>♪ Are you gonna ride? ♪</i>

104
00:06:09.403 --> 00:06:11.403
[♪♪♪]

105
00:06:22.182 --> 00:06:23.548
[METALLIC THUD]

106
00:06:38.365 --> 00:06:39.648
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS]

107
00:06:50.610 --> 00:06:52.777
[BOTH GRUNTING]

108
00:07:03.389 --> 00:07:05.189
Whoa. easy. tiger.

109
00:07:06.059 --> 00:07:07.036
Dean?

110
00:07:07.060 --> 00:07:08.404
[CHUCKLES]

111
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.172
You scared the crap out of me.

112
00:07:10.196 --> 00:07:11.329
You're outta practice.

113
00:07:13.299 --> 00:07:15.059
[CHUCKLES] Or not.

114
00:07:15.569 --> 00:07:17.079
Get off me.

115
00:07:17.103 --> 00:07:18.748
Dean. what the hell
are you doing here?

116
00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:21.116
I was looking for a beer.

117
00:07:21.140 --> 00:07:23.152
What the hell are
you doing here?

118
00:07:23.176 --> 00:07:25.421
Okay. all right. We gotta talk.

119
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:26.722
Uh. the phone?

120
00:07:26.746 --> 00:07:28.625
If I had called. would
you have picked up?

121
00:07:28.649 --> 00:07:29.649
Sam?

122
00:07:30.717 --> 00:07:32.045
SAM: Jess.

123
00:07:32.069 --> 00:07:33.946
Hey. Uh...

124
00:07:33.970 --> 00:07:36.599
Dean. this is my
girlfriend. Jessica.

125
00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:37.783
JESSICA: Wait.

126
00:07:37.807 --> 00:07:39.102
Your brother Dean?

127
00:07:39.126 --> 00:07:40.403
I love the Smurfs.

128
00:07:40.427 --> 00:07:43.306
You know. I gotta tell you.

129
00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:45.441
you are completely out
of my brother's league.

130
00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.276
Let me put something
on. No. no. no.

131
00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:48.711
I wouldn't dream of it.

132
00:07:48.735 --> 00:07:49.862
Seriously.

133
00:07:49.886 --> 00:07:52.364
Anyway. I gotta borrow
your boyfriend here.

134
00:07:52.388 --> 00:07:54.166
talk about some
private family business.

135
00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:55.757
But. uh. nice meeting you.

136
00:07:57.544 --> 00:07:58.521
No.

137
00:07:58.545 --> 00:08:00.390
No.

138
00:08:00.414 --> 00:08:02.659
Whatever you wanna say.
you can say it in front of her.

139
00:08:02.683 --> 00:08:04.560
Okay.

140
00:08:04.584 --> 00:08:07.062
Um. Dad hasn't been
home in a few days.

141
00:08:07.086 --> 00:08:10.366
So he's working overtime
on a "Miller Time" shift.

142
00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:12.470
He'll stumble back
in sooner or later.

143
00:08:14.343 --> 00:08:16.622
Dad's on a hunting trip.

144
00:08:16.646 --> 00:08:18.808
And he hasn't been
home in a few days.

145
00:08:18.832 --> 00:08:20.832
[♪♪♪]

146
00:08:23.203 --> 00:08:25.648
Jess. excuse us.

147
00:08:25.672 --> 00:08:28.468
We have to go outside.

148
00:08:28.492 --> 00:08:29.668
SAM: I mean. come on.

149
00:08:29.692 --> 00:08:31.571
you can't just break
in. middle of the night.

150
00:08:31.595 --> 00:08:33.172
and expect me to
hit the road with you.

151
00:08:33.196 --> 00:08:34.740
DEAN: You're not
hearing me. Sammy.

152
00:08:34.764 --> 00:08:36.642
Dad's missing. I need
you to help me find him.

153
00:08:36.666 --> 00:08:38.877
SAM: You remember
the poltergeist in Amherst?

154
00:08:38.901 --> 00:08:41.414
Or the Devil's Gates in
Clifton? He was missing then too.

155
00:08:41.438 --> 00:08:43.349
He's always missing.
and he's always fine.

156
00:08:43.373 --> 00:08:44.417
Not for this long.

157
00:08:44.441 --> 00:08:46.118
Now. you gonna
come with me or not?

158
00:08:46.142 --> 00:08:48.320
I'm not. Why not?

159
00:08:48.344 --> 00:08:51.007
I swore I was done
hunting. For good.

160
00:08:51.031 --> 00:08:52.942
It wasn't easy. but
it wasn't that bad.

161
00:08:52.966 --> 00:08:54.343
Yeah?

162
00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:56.546
When I told Dad I was
scared of the thing in my closet.

163
00:08:56.570 --> 00:08:57.547
he gave me a .45.

164
00:08:57.571 --> 00:08:58.715
What was he supposed to do?

165
00:08:58.739 --> 00:09:01.083
I was 9 years old.

166
00:09:01.107 --> 00:09:03.336
He was supposed to say.
"Don't be afraid of the dark."

167
00:09:03.360 --> 00:09:04.653
"Don't be afraid of the dark"?

168
00:09:04.677 --> 00:09:06.673
You kidding me? Of
course you should be afraid.

169
00:09:06.697 --> 00:09:08.190
You know what's
out there. I know.

170
00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:10.292
But still. the way we grew
up. after Mom was killed

171
00:09:10.316 --> 00:09:12.595
and Dad's obsession to
find the thing that killed her.

172
00:09:12.619 --> 00:09:14.898
But we still haven't
found the damn thing.

173
00:09:14.922 --> 00:09:16.900
So we kill everything
we can find.

174
00:09:16.924 --> 00:09:18.873
Save a lot of
people doing it too.

175
00:09:21.395 --> 00:09:23.755
You think Mom would
have wanted this for us?

176
00:09:25.849 --> 00:09:27.176
SAM: The weapon training?

177
00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:29.428
And melting the
silver into bullets?

178
00:09:29.452 --> 00:09:31.830
Man. Dean. we were
raised like warriors.

179
00:09:31.854 --> 00:09:32.965
So. what are you gonna do?

180
00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:35.968
You just gonna live some
normal. apple-pie life?

181
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:36.969
Is that it?

182
00:09:36.993 --> 00:09:38.003
No. Not normal.

183
00:09:38.027 --> 00:09:39.555
Safe.

184
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:41.341
And that's why you ran away.

185
00:09:41.365 --> 00:09:42.405
[SCOFFS]

186
00:09:44.701 --> 00:09:46.812
I was just going to college.

187
00:09:46.836 --> 00:09:49.704
It was Dad who said if I was
gonna go. I should stay gone.

188
00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:52.402
And that's what I'm doing.

189
00:09:52.426 --> 00:09:54.303
Yeah. well. Dad's in
real trouble right now.

190
00:09:54.327 --> 00:09:56.687
if he's not dead
already. I can feel it.

191
00:09:59.065 --> 00:10:00.426
I can't do this alone.

192
00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:01.894
Yes. you can.

193
00:10:01.918 --> 00:10:05.186
Yeah. Well. I don't want to.

194
00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:10.391
[SIGHS]

195
00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:15.196
What was he hunting?

196
00:10:20.420 --> 00:10:21.664
DEAN: All right.

197
00:10:21.688 --> 00:10:24.300
Let's see. Where the
hell did I put that thing?

198
00:10:24.324 --> 00:10:26.285
So when Dad left. why
didn't you go with him?

199
00:10:26.309 --> 00:10:27.970
I was working my own gig.

200
00:10:27.994 --> 00:10:29.688
This voodoo thing
down in New Orleans.

201
00:10:29.712 --> 00:10:32.541
Dad let you go on a
hunting trip by yourself?

202
00:10:32.565 --> 00:10:35.033
I'm 26. dude.

203
00:10:36.153 --> 00:10:37.296
All right. Here we go.

204
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:40.566
So Dad was checking
out this two-lane blacktop

205
00:10:40.590 --> 00:10:42.452
just outside of
Jericho. California.

206
00:10:42.476 --> 00:10:44.053
About a month ago. this guy.

207
00:10:44.077 --> 00:10:47.144
They found his car. but he'd
vanished. Completely MIA.

208
00:10:48.348 --> 00:10:49.608
So maybe he was kidnapped.

209
00:10:49.632 --> 00:10:51.894
Yeah. well. Here's
another one in April.

210
00:10:51.918 --> 00:10:53.496
Another in December '04.

211
00:10:53.520 --> 00:10:55.130
'03. '98. '92.

212
00:10:55.154 --> 00:10:56.131
Ten of 'em

213
00:10:56.155 --> 00:10:57.155
over the past 20 years.

214
00:10:57.824 --> 00:10:59.001
All men.

215
00:10:59.025 --> 00:11:01.065
all the same five-mile
stretch of road.

216
00:11:02.445 --> 00:11:04.790
It started happening
more and more.

217
00:11:04.814 --> 00:11:06.359
so Dad went to go dig around.

218
00:11:06.383 --> 00:11:08.327
That was about three weeks ago.

219
00:11:08.351 --> 00:11:11.780
I hadn't heard from him
since. which is bad enough.

220
00:11:11.804 --> 00:11:14.183
Then I get this
voice mail yesterday.

221
00:11:14.207 --> 00:11:16.936
JOHN [THROUGH STATIC]: <i>Dean.
Something is starting to happen.</i>

222
00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:19.955
<i>I think it's serious.</i>

223
00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:21.658
<i>I need to try to find
out what's going on.</i>

224
00:11:21.682 --> 00:11:23.926
<i>It may be... looking...</i>

225
00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:25.461
<i>Be very careful. Dean.</i>

226
00:11:25.485 --> 00:11:27.496
<i>We're all in danger.</i>

227
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.832
You know there's E.V.P. on that?

228
00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:32.001
Not bad. Sammy. Kind
of like riding a bike. isn't it?

229
00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:33.920
All right.

230
00:11:33.944 --> 00:11:35.388
I slowed the message down

231
00:11:35.412 --> 00:11:36.672
and ran it through a Goldwave.

232
00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:39.136
Took out the hiss
and this is what I got.

233
00:11:40.499 --> 00:11:42.350
WOMAN: <i>I can never go home.</i>

234
00:11:45.355 --> 00:11:47.438
"Never go home."

235
00:11:52.895 --> 00:11:54.206
You know. in almost two years.

236
00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:56.964
I've never bothered you.
never asked you for a thing.

237
00:11:58.601 --> 00:11:59.601
[SIGHS]

238
00:12:04.241 --> 00:12:05.940
All right. I'll go.

239
00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:08.854
I'll help you find him.

240
00:12:08.878 --> 00:12:11.007
But I have to get back
first thing Monday.

241
00:12:11.031 --> 00:12:12.825
Just wait here.

242
00:12:12.849 --> 00:12:14.148
What's first thing Monday?

243
00:12:16.085 --> 00:12:17.936
I have this...

244
00:12:19.222 --> 00:12:20.199
I have an interview.

245
00:12:20.223 --> 00:12:22.504
What. a job interview? Skip it.

246
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:25.737
It's a law school interview.

247
00:12:25.761 --> 00:12:28.157
and it's my whole
future on a plate.

248
00:12:28.181 --> 00:12:29.591
Law school?

249
00:12:29.615 --> 00:12:31.749
So we got a deal or not?

250
00:12:35.454 --> 00:12:37.432
Wait. you're taking off?

251
00:12:37.456 --> 00:12:39.401
Is this about your
dad? Is he all right?

252
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:41.837
Yeah. You know. just
a little family drama.

253
00:12:41.861 --> 00:12:44.807
Your brother said he was
on some kind of hunting trip?

254
00:12:44.831 --> 00:12:48.043
Oh. yeah. he's just deer
hunti" up at the cabin.

255
00:12:48.067 --> 00:12:50.813
He's probably got Jim.
Jack. and Jose along with him.

256
00:12:50.837 --> 00:12:52.314
We're just gonna
go bring him back.

257
00:12:52.338 --> 00:12:54.449
What about the interview?

258
00:12:54.473 --> 00:12:57.519
I'll make the interview. This
is only for a couple days.

259
00:12:57.543 --> 00:13:00.189
Sam. I mean. please.
Just stop for a second.

260
00:13:00.213 --> 00:13:02.391
You sure you're okay?

261
00:13:02.415 --> 00:13:04.210
Heh. I'm fine.

262
00:13:04.234 --> 00:13:06.229
It's just...

263
00:13:06.253 --> 00:13:08.030
you won't even talk
about your family.

264
00:13:08.054 --> 00:13:10.198
And now you're taking
off in the middle of the night

265
00:13:10.222 --> 00:13:11.867
to spend the weekend with them?

266
00:13:11.891 --> 00:13:14.420
And with Monday coming up.
which is kind of a huge deal.

267
00:13:14.444 --> 00:13:15.437
Hey.

268
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:17.372
everything's gonna be okay.

269
00:13:17.396 --> 00:13:20.281
I will be back in
time. I promise.

270
00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:26.048
At least tell me
where you're going.

271
00:13:26.072 --> 00:13:29.232
[EAGLES OF DEATH METAL'S "SPEAKING
IN TONGUES" PLAYING OVER RADIO]

272
00:13:35.115 --> 00:13:37.743
Amy. I can't come over tonight.

273
00:13:37.767 --> 00:13:40.668
B-because I got work in
the morning. that's why.

274
00:13:42.071 --> 00:13:44.950
Okay. I miss it. my
dad's gonna have my ass.

275
00:13:44.974 --> 00:13:46.140
[CHUCKLES]

276
00:13:50.179 --> 00:13:52.491
Hey. uh. Amy. let
me call you back?

277
00:13:52.515 --> 00:13:54.594
<i>♪ I got this feeling And
it's deep in my body ♪</i>

278
00:13:54.618 --> 00:13:57.663
<i>♪ It gives me wiggles And
it makes my rump shake ♪</i>

279
00:13:57.687 --> 00:13:59.782
[RADIO BREAKING UP]

280
00:13:59.806 --> 00:14:01.288
[♪♪♪]

281
00:14:05.128 --> 00:14:06.728
Car trouble or somethin'?

282
00:14:11.885 --> 00:14:13.467
Take me home.

283
00:14:14.904 --> 00:14:15.920
Sure. Get in.

284
00:14:33.106 --> 00:14:35.673
So where do you live? Heh.

285
00:14:38.310 --> 00:14:40.973
At the end of Breckenridge Road.

286
00:14:40.997 --> 00:14:45.115
You coming. uh. from a
Halloween party or somethin'?

287
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.080
[LAUGHS]

288
00:14:49.104 --> 00:14:50.215
You know. um.

289
00:14:50.239 --> 00:14:51.233
a girl like you really

290
00:14:51.257 --> 00:14:52.924
shouldn't be alone out here.

291
00:15:05.104 --> 00:15:06.587
I'm with you.

292
00:15:17.466 --> 00:15:19.466
Do you think I'm pretty?

293
00:15:20.386 --> 00:15:21.386
Uh-huh.

294
00:15:24.357 --> 00:15:26.068
Will you come home with me?

295
00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:28.053
Um...

296
00:15:28.077 --> 00:15:29.605
Hell. yeah.

297
00:15:29.629 --> 00:15:30.962
[TIRES SQUEALING]

298
00:15:48.130 --> 00:15:50.409
Come on.

299
00:15:50.433 --> 00:15:52.277
You don't live here.

300
00:15:52.301 --> 00:15:54.579
I can never go home.

301
00:15:54.603 --> 00:15:56.716
What? What are
you talking about?

302
00:15:56.740 --> 00:15:58.450
Nobody even lives here.

303
00:15:58.474 --> 00:16:00.691
Huh? Where do you live?

304
00:16:07.183 --> 00:16:10.029
Heh. That was good.

305
00:16:10.053 --> 00:16:12.403
Joke's over. okay?

306
00:16:14.890 --> 00:16:16.240
You want me to leave?

307
00:16:36.429 --> 00:16:37.429
Hello?

308
00:16:44.804 --> 00:16:46.570
Hello?

309
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:55.246
[SCREAMS]

310
00:17:25.962 --> 00:17:28.980
[TROY SCREAMING]

311
00:17:38.891 --> 00:17:41.170
[ALLMAN BROTHERS BAND'S
"RAMBLIN' MAN" PLAYING]

312
00:17:41.194 --> 00:17:43.638
<i>♪ Lord. I was born
A ramblin' man ♪</i>

313
00:17:43.662 --> 00:17:45.540
[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

314
00:17:45.564 --> 00:17:48.243
Hey. You want breakfast?

315
00:17:48.267 --> 00:17:50.312
No. thanks.

316
00:17:50.336 --> 00:17:52.014
So how'd you pay for that stuff?

317
00:17:52.038 --> 00:17:54.483
You and Dad still
running credit card scams?

318
00:17:54.507 --> 00:17:57.741
Yeah. well. hunting ain't
exactly a pro-ball career.

319
00:17:59.212 --> 00:18:00.389
Besides. all we do is apply.

320
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:02.157
It's not our fault they
send us the cards.

321
00:18:02.181 --> 00:18:03.558
Yeah?

322
00:18:03.582 --> 00:18:06.028
And what names did you write
on the application this time?

323
00:18:06.052 --> 00:18:07.029
DEAN: Uh...

324
00:18:07.053 --> 00:18:08.364
Burt Aframian

325
00:18:08.388 --> 00:18:10.533
and his son Hector.

326
00:18:10.557 --> 00:18:11.934
Scored two cards
out of the deal.

327
00:18:11.958 --> 00:18:13.268
Sounds about right.

328
00:18:13.292 --> 00:18:14.754
I swear. man.

329
00:18:14.778 --> 00:18:17.623
You gotta update your
cassette tape collection. Why?

330
00:18:17.647 --> 00:18:19.542
Well. for one. they're
cassette tapes.

331
00:18:19.566 --> 00:18:20.609
And two...

332
00:18:20.633 --> 00:18:22.178
Black Sabbath?

333
00:18:22.202 --> 00:18:23.763
Motörhead?

334
00:18:23.787 --> 00:18:25.381
Metallica?

335
00:18:25.405 --> 00:18:27.883
It's the greatest hits
of mullet rock. Yeah...

336
00:18:27.907 --> 00:18:29.351
House rules. Sammy.

337
00:18:29.375 --> 00:18:30.519
Driver picks the music.

338
00:18:30.543 --> 00:18:32.888
shotgun shuts his cake-hole.

339
00:18:32.912 --> 00:18:34.757
You know. "Sammy"
is a chubby 12-year-old.

340
00:18:34.781 --> 00:18:36.108
It's Sam. okay?

341
00:18:36.132 --> 00:18:39.862
Sorry. I can't hear you.
The music's too loud.

342
00:18:39.886 --> 00:18:42.786
[AC/DC'S "BACK IN BLACK"
PLAYING OVER RADIO]

343
00:18:46.525 --> 00:18:47.836
<i>♪ Back in black ♪</i>

344
00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.504
<i>♪ I hit the sack ♪</i>

345
00:18:49.528 --> 00:18:51.606
<i>♪ I've been too long
I'm glad to be back ♪</i>

346
00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:54.009
<i>♪ Yes. I'm let loose
From the noose ♪</i>

347
00:18:54.033 --> 00:18:55.510
<i>♪ That's kept me
Hanging about... ♪</i>

348
00:18:55.534 --> 00:18:57.094
SAM: Thank you.

349
00:18:57.770 --> 00:18:59.582
All right. so there's
no one matching Dad

350
00:18:59.606 --> 00:19:01.167
at the hospital or morgue.

351
00:19:01.191 --> 00:19:03.719
So that's something. I guess.

352
00:19:03.743 --> 00:19:05.304
<i>♪ Cat's eyes ♪</i>

353
00:19:05.328 --> 00:19:07.056
Check it out.

354
00:19:07.080 --> 00:19:10.176
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm back
Yes. I'm back ♪</i>

355
00:19:10.200 --> 00:19:12.667
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

356
00:19:17.841 --> 00:19:19.640
[♪♪♪]

357
00:19:30.436 --> 00:19:31.485
Let's go.

358
00:19:35.474 --> 00:19:37.252
You guys find anything?

359
00:19:37.276 --> 00:19:39.476
No! Nothing!

360
00:19:43.482 --> 00:19:44.727
[EXHALES]

361
00:19:44.751 --> 00:19:46.261
No sign of struggle.

362
00:19:46.285 --> 00:19:48.547
No footprints. No fingerprints.

363
00:19:48.571 --> 00:19:50.149
Spotless. It's almost too clean.

364
00:19:50.173 --> 00:19:51.550
So this kid Troy.

365
00:19:51.574 --> 00:19:53.519
he's dating your
daughter. isn't he? Yeah.

366
00:19:53.543 --> 00:19:55.304
How's Amy doin'?

367
00:19:55.328 --> 00:19:57.272
She's putting up missing
posters downtown.

368
00:19:57.296 --> 00:19:59.141
DEAN: You fellas had
another one like this

369
00:19:59.165 --> 00:20:01.065
just last month. didn't you?

370
00:20:01.984 --> 00:20:03.312
And who are you?

371
00:20:03.336 --> 00:20:04.802
Federal marshals.

372
00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.717
You two are a little young
for marshals. aren't you?

373
00:20:08.741 --> 00:20:10.919
Ha. Thanks. That's
awfully kind of you.

374
00:20:10.943 --> 00:20:13.322
You did have another
one just like this. correct?

375
00:20:13.346 --> 00:20:15.491
Yeah. that's right.
About a mile up the road.

376
00:20:15.515 --> 00:20:16.992
There've been
others before that.

377
00:20:17.016 --> 00:20:18.159
So this victim...

378
00:20:18.183 --> 00:20:19.245
you knew him?

379
00:20:19.269 --> 00:20:22.131
Town like this. everybody
knows everybody.

380
00:20:22.155 --> 00:20:23.832
Any connection
between the victims.

381
00:20:23.856 --> 00:20:25.501
besides that they're all men?

382
00:20:25.525 --> 00:20:27.303
No. not so far as we can tell.

383
00:20:27.327 --> 00:20:28.304
So. what's the theory?

384
00:20:28.328 --> 00:20:29.738
Honestly? We don't know.

385
00:20:29.762 --> 00:20:30.756
Serial murder?

386
00:20:30.780 --> 00:20:31.790
Kidnapping ring?

387
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:33.142
DEAN: That is exactly the kind

388
00:20:33.166 --> 00:20:35.933
of crack police work I'd
expect out of you guys.

389
00:20:36.836 --> 00:20:38.168
Thank you for your time.

390
00:20:39.172 --> 00:20:40.287
Gentlemen.

391
00:20:48.464 --> 00:20:49.774
Ow. What was that for?

392
00:20:49.798 --> 00:20:51.043
Why you gotta step on my foot?

393
00:20:51.067 --> 00:20:52.710
Why do you talk
to police like that?

394
00:20:52.734 --> 00:20:53.996
Come on.

395
00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:55.998
They don't really
know what's going on.

396
00:20:56.022 --> 00:20:57.249
We're all alone on this.

397
00:20:57.273 --> 00:20:58.316
If we're gonna find Dad.

398
00:20:58.340 --> 00:21:00.369
we gotta get to the
bottom of this ourselves.

399
00:21:00.393 --> 00:21:02.454
[CLEARS THROAT]

400
00:21:02.478 --> 00:21:03.789
Can I help you boys?

401
00:21:03.813 --> 00:21:06.542
No. sir. We were just leaving.

402
00:21:06.566 --> 00:21:07.676
Agent Mulder.

403
00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:09.099
Agent Scully.

404
00:21:16.959 --> 00:21:18.570
DEAN: I'll bet you that's her.

405
00:21:18.594 --> 00:21:19.794
Yeah.

406
00:21:21.363 --> 00:21:22.340
You must be Amy.

407
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:23.608
Yeah.

408
00:21:23.632 --> 00:21:25.610
Yeah. Troy told us about
you. We're his uncles.

409
00:21:25.634 --> 00:21:26.745
I'm Dean. This is Sammy.

410
00:21:26.769 --> 00:21:28.647
He never mentioned you to me.

411
00:21:28.671 --> 00:21:30.082
Well. that's Troy. I guess.

412
00:21:30.106 --> 00:21:31.950
We're not around much.
we're up in Modesto.

413
00:21:31.974 --> 00:21:33.252
So we're looking for him too.

414
00:21:33.276 --> 00:21:35.754
and we're kinda asking around.

415
00:21:35.778 --> 00:21:36.989
Hey. are you okay?

416
00:21:37.013 --> 00:21:38.157
Yeah.

417
00:21:38.181 --> 00:21:40.242
You mind if we ask
you a couple questions?

418
00:21:40.266 --> 00:21:42.828
AMY: <i>I was on the
phone with Troy.</i>

419
00:21:42.852 --> 00:21:44.563
He was driving home.

420
00:21:44.587 --> 00:21:47.700
He said he would call
me right back. And. uh...

421
00:21:47.724 --> 00:21:48.767
he never did.

422
00:21:48.791 --> 00:21:50.369
SAM: He didn't say
anything strange?

423
00:21:50.393 --> 00:21:52.638
Or out of the ordinary? No.

424
00:21:52.662 --> 00:21:53.960
Nothing I can remember.

425
00:21:55.981 --> 00:21:57.848
I like your necklace.

426
00:21:59.902 --> 00:22:02.064
Troy gave it to me.

427
00:22:02.088 --> 00:22:03.315
Mostly to scare my parents...

428
00:22:03.339 --> 00:22:04.416
[LAUGHS]

429
00:22:04.440 --> 00:22:06.151
with all that devil stuff.

430
00:22:06.175 --> 00:22:08.353
[LAUGHS]

431
00:22:08.377 --> 00:22:09.354
Actually.

432
00:22:09.378 --> 00:22:10.839
it means just the opposite.

433
00:22:10.863 --> 00:22:13.308
A pentagram is
protection against evil.

434
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:14.509
Really powerful.

435
00:22:14.533 --> 00:22:17.412
I mean. if you believe
in that kind of thing.

436
00:22:17.436 --> 00:22:19.214
Okay. Thank you.
<i>Unsolved Mysteries.</i>

437
00:22:19.238 --> 00:22:20.883
Here's the deal. ladies.

438
00:22:20.907 --> 00:22:22.651
The way Troy disappeared...

439
00:22:22.675 --> 00:22:24.369
something's not right.

440
00:22:24.393 --> 00:22:26.076
So if you've heard anything...

441
00:22:27.814 --> 00:22:29.124
What is it?

442
00:22:29.148 --> 00:22:31.359
Well. it's just...

443
00:22:31.383 --> 00:22:34.213
I mean. with all these guys
going missing. people talk.

444
00:22:34.237 --> 00:22:36.077
BOTH: What do they talk about?

445
00:22:38.874 --> 00:22:41.186
It's kind of this local legend.

446
00:22:41.210 --> 00:22:44.940
This one girl. she got
murdered out on Centennial.

447
00:22:44.964 --> 00:22:46.442
like. decades ago.

448
00:22:46.466 --> 00:22:49.445
Well. supposedly
she's still out there.

449
00:22:49.469 --> 00:22:51.179
She hitchhikes.

450
00:22:51.203 --> 00:22:53.415
And whoever picks her up.

451
00:22:53.439 --> 00:22:56.439
well. they disappear forever.

452
00:22:58.010 --> 00:22:59.643
[TYPING]

453
00:23:14.026 --> 00:23:15.546
Let me try. Got it.

454
00:23:16.412 --> 00:23:17.692
Dude!

455
00:23:18.748 --> 00:23:20.413
You're such a control freak.

456
00:23:21.751 --> 00:23:24.045
So angry spirits are born
out of violent death. right?

457
00:23:24.069 --> 00:23:26.648
Yeah. But maybe it's not murder.

458
00:23:26.672 --> 00:23:28.672
[♪♪♪]

459
00:23:34.997 --> 00:23:36.775
This was 1981.

460
00:23:36.799 --> 00:23:38.176
"Constance Welch. 24 years old.

461
00:23:38.200 --> 00:23:40.996
jumps off Sylvania
Bridge. Drowns in the river."

462
00:23:41.020 --> 00:23:42.447
Say why she did it? Yeah.

463
00:23:42.471 --> 00:23:43.948
Why?

464
00:23:43.972 --> 00:23:46.785
An hour before they
found her. she calls 911.

465
00:23:46.809 --> 00:23:48.270
Her two kids are in the bathtub.

466
00:23:48.294 --> 00:23:49.755
She leaves them
alone for a minute.

467
00:23:49.779 --> 00:23:52.078
and when she comes
back. they aren't breathing.

468
00:23:52.982 --> 00:23:54.843
Both die. Hm.

469
00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:56.044
"'Our babies were gone.

470
00:23:56.068 --> 00:23:57.846
"and Constance
just couldn't bear it. '

471
00:23:57.870 --> 00:24:00.382
said husband Joseph Welch."

472
00:24:00.406 --> 00:24:02.646
DEAN: That bridge
look familiar to you?

473
00:24:08.214 --> 00:24:10.725
So this is where Constance
took the swan dive.

474
00:24:10.749 --> 00:24:12.782
So you think Dad
would have been here?

475
00:24:14.286 --> 00:24:16.806
Well. he's chasing the same
story. and we're chasing him.

476
00:24:18.106 --> 00:24:20.318
Okay. so now what?

477
00:24:20.342 --> 00:24:21.886
Now we keep
digging till we find him.

478
00:24:21.910 --> 00:24:23.455
Might take a while.

479
00:24:23.479 --> 00:24:25.907
Dean. I told you. I've
gotta get back by...

480
00:24:25.931 --> 00:24:27.943
By Monday.

481
00:24:27.967 --> 00:24:28.994
Right.

482
00:24:29.018 --> 00:24:30.078
The interview. Yeah.

483
00:24:30.102 --> 00:24:32.080
Yeah. I forgot.

484
00:24:32.104 --> 00:24:34.682
You're really serious
about this. aren't you?

485
00:24:34.706 --> 00:24:37.369
You think you're just
gonna become some lawyer?

486
00:24:37.393 --> 00:24:38.837
Marry your girl?

487
00:24:38.861 --> 00:24:40.155
Maybe. Why not?

488
00:24:40.179 --> 00:24:41.406
Does Jessica know the truth?

489
00:24:41.430 --> 00:24:43.625
Does she know about
the things you've done?

490
00:24:43.649 --> 00:24:45.560
No. And she's not
ever going to know.

491
00:24:45.584 --> 00:24:47.729
Well. that's healthy.

492
00:24:47.753 --> 00:24:49.815
You can pretend all
you want. Sammy.

493
00:24:49.839 --> 00:24:52.600
but you're gonna have
to face up to who you are.

494
00:24:52.624 --> 00:24:54.636
And who's that?
You're one of us.

495
00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:56.271
No. I'm not like you.

496
00:24:56.295 --> 00:24:58.106
This is not going to be my life.

497
00:24:58.130 --> 00:25:00.275
Well. you have a
responsibility. To Dad?

498
00:25:00.299 --> 00:25:01.910
And his crusade?

499
00:25:01.934 --> 00:25:03.745
If it weren't for pictures.

500
00:25:03.769 --> 00:25:05.897
I wouldn't even know
what Mom looks like.

501
00:25:05.921 --> 00:25:07.399
And what difference
would it make?

502
00:25:07.423 --> 00:25:10.585
Even if we do find
the thing that killed her.

503
00:25:10.609 --> 00:25:13.010
Mom's gone. and
she isn't coming back.

504
00:25:19.268 --> 00:25:21.618
Don't talk about her like that.

505
00:25:31.263 --> 00:25:32.340
Sam.

506
00:25:32.364 --> 00:25:35.249
[♪♪♪]

507
00:25:44.726 --> 00:25:46.788
Where'd she go? I don't know.

508
00:25:46.812 --> 00:25:48.144
[ENGINE STARTS]

509
00:25:50.766 --> 00:25:52.644
What the...?

510
00:25:52.668 --> 00:25:53.948
Who's driving your car?

511
00:26:02.945 --> 00:26:03.978
Go. Go!

512
00:26:24.433 --> 00:26:26.299
[SAM GRUNTING]

513
00:26:29.838 --> 00:26:30.838
Dean!

514
00:26:32.024 --> 00:26:33.156
Dean!

515
00:26:35.794 --> 00:26:37.427
What?

516
00:26:40.366 --> 00:26:42.299
Hey. are you all right?

517
00:26:43.568 --> 00:26:45.335
I'm super.

518
00:26:50.542 --> 00:26:51.953
Car all right?

519
00:26:51.977 --> 00:26:54.723
Yeah. Whatever she did
to it. it seems all right now.

520
00:26:54.747 --> 00:26:57.092
That Constance
chick. what a bitch!

521
00:26:57.116 --> 00:26:58.894
Well. she doesn't
want us digging around.

522
00:26:58.918 --> 00:26:59.918
that's for sure.

523
00:27:01.787 --> 00:27:03.687
So where's the trail
go from here. genius?

524
00:27:09.645 --> 00:27:11.145
You smell like a toilet.

525
00:27:14.684 --> 00:27:15.684
One room. please.

526
00:27:19.105 --> 00:27:21.499
You guys having a
reunion or somethin'?

527
00:27:21.523 --> 00:27:22.633
What do you mean?

528
00:27:22.657 --> 00:27:24.469
That other guy. Burt Aframian.

529
00:27:24.493 --> 00:27:27.055
He came in and bought out
a room for the whole month.

530
00:27:27.079 --> 00:27:29.724
<i>[DOOR UNLOCKING]</i>

531
00:27:29.748 --> 00:27:31.732
[♪♪♪]

532
00:27:44.863 --> 00:27:46.679
Whoa.

533
00:27:54.940 --> 00:27:57.118
[GROANS]

534
00:27:57.142 --> 00:27:59.662
I don't think he's been here
for a couple of days. at least.

535
00:28:02.214 --> 00:28:05.460
Salt. Cat's eye shells.

536
00:28:05.484 --> 00:28:08.785
He was worried. Trying to
keep something from coming in.

537
00:28:11.957 --> 00:28:13.802
What do you got here?

538
00:28:13.826 --> 00:28:15.692
Centennial Highway victims.

539
00:28:17.896 --> 00:28:19.474
I don't get it.

540
00:28:19.498 --> 00:28:20.809
They're different men.

541
00:28:20.833 --> 00:28:23.744
different jobs.
ages. ethnicities...

542
00:28:23.768 --> 00:28:27.015
There's always a
connection. right?

543
00:28:27.039 --> 00:28:28.771
What do these guys
have in common?

544
00:28:43.556 --> 00:28:44.783
Dad figured it out.

545
00:28:44.807 --> 00:28:46.151
What do you mean?

546
00:28:46.175 --> 00:28:48.703
He found the
same article we did.

547
00:28:48.727 --> 00:28:50.288
Constance Welch.

548
00:28:50.312 --> 00:28:51.929
She's a "Woman in White."

549
00:28:54.733 --> 00:28:56.595
You sly dogs.

550
00:28:56.619 --> 00:28:58.262
If we're dealing with
a Woman in White.

551
00:28:58.286 --> 00:29:00.131
Dad would find the
corpse and destroyed it.

552
00:29:00.155 --> 00:29:02.400
She might have another weakness.

553
00:29:02.424 --> 00:29:04.035
No. Dad would wanna make sure.

554
00:29:04.059 --> 00:29:06.104
He'd dig her up. Does it
say where she's buried?

555
00:29:06.128 --> 00:29:08.740
SAM: No. Not that I can tell.

556
00:29:08.764 --> 00:29:10.075
If I were Dad. though.

557
00:29:10.099 --> 00:29:11.193
I'd go ask her husband.

558
00:29:11.217 --> 00:29:12.994
If he's still alive.

559
00:29:13.018 --> 00:29:14.851
DEAN: Hm.

560
00:29:18.957 --> 00:29:20.168
All right.

561
00:29:20.192 --> 00:29:22.037
why don't you see if
you can find an address.

562
00:29:22.061 --> 00:29:23.861
I'm gonna clean up. Hey. Dean?

563
00:29:24.797 --> 00:29:26.007
What I said earlier.

564
00:29:26.031 --> 00:29:28.111
about Mom and Dad. I'm sorry...

565
00:29:28.751 --> 00:29:30.250
No chick flick moments.

566
00:29:31.469 --> 00:29:33.714
All right. Jerk.

567
00:29:33.738 --> 00:29:35.717
Bitch.

568
00:29:35.741 --> 00:29:37.541
[CHUCKLES]

569
00:29:52.441 --> 00:29:54.586
JESSICA [ON VOICE
MAIL]: <i>Hey. it's me.</i>

570
00:29:54.610 --> 00:29:56.655
<i>It's about 10:20.
Saturday night...</i>

571
00:29:56.679 --> 00:29:58.389
Hey. man. I'm starving.

572
00:29:58.413 --> 00:30:00.792
I'm gonna grab a little
something to eat at that diner.

573
00:30:00.816 --> 00:30:02.293
You want anything?

574
00:30:02.317 --> 00:30:04.162
No. Aframian's buying.

575
00:30:04.186 --> 00:30:05.306
Uh-uh.

576
00:30:05.938 --> 00:30:07.938
[♪♪♪]

577
00:30:17.783 --> 00:30:19.249
<i>[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]</i>

578
00:30:21.837 --> 00:30:24.182
JESSICA: <i>So come home
soon. okay? I love you.</i>

579
00:30:24.206 --> 00:30:25.286
[BEEPS]

580
00:30:26.875 --> 00:30:27.853
What?

581
00:30:27.877 --> 00:30:29.521
Dude. Five-O. Take off.

582
00:30:29.545 --> 00:30:31.022
What about you?

583
00:30:31.046 --> 00:30:33.263
<i>Uh. they kinda spotted
me. Go find Dad.</i>

584
00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:36.361
Problem. officers?

585
00:30:36.385 --> 00:30:37.696
Where's your partner?

586
00:30:37.720 --> 00:30:40.187
Partner. what...? What partner?

587
00:30:48.030 --> 00:30:51.710
So. Fake U.S. marshal.
Fake credit cards.

588
00:30:51.734 --> 00:30:53.545
You got anything that's real?

589
00:30:53.569 --> 00:30:54.935
My boobs.

590
00:30:56.621 --> 00:30:59.181
You have the right
to remain silent.

591
00:31:04.129 --> 00:31:06.141
So you wanna give
us your real name?

592
00:31:06.165 --> 00:31:09.766
I told you. It's
Nugent. Ted Nugent.

593
00:31:11.570 --> 00:31:13.281
I'm not sure you realize

594
00:31:13.305 --> 00:31:15.166
just how much
trouble you're in here.

595
00:31:15.190 --> 00:31:17.285
We talking. like.
misdemeanor kind of trouble?

596
00:31:17.309 --> 00:31:19.654
Or. uh.
"Squeal-like-a-pig" trouble?

597
00:31:19.678 --> 00:31:20.722
You got the faces

598
00:31:20.746 --> 00:31:22.557
of 10 missing persons
taped to your wall

599
00:31:22.581 --> 00:31:25.594
along with a whole lot
of satanic mumbo jumbo.

600
00:31:25.618 --> 00:31:27.828
Boy. you are
officially a suspect.

601
00:31:27.852 --> 00:31:29.347
That makes sense.

602
00:31:29.371 --> 00:31:32.484
'Cause when the first one
went missing in '82. I was 3.

603
00:31:32.508 --> 00:31:36.304
I know you got partners.
One of theme's an older guy.

604
00:31:36.328 --> 00:31:38.861
Maybe he started
the whole thing.

605
00:31:39.982 --> 00:31:41.610
So tell me.

606
00:31:41.634 --> 00:31:43.166
Dean.

607
00:31:44.703 --> 00:31:45.718
Is this his?

608
00:31:53.061 --> 00:31:54.527
I thought that
might be your name.

609
00:31:55.964 --> 00:31:58.159
See. I leafed through this.

610
00:31:58.183 --> 00:31:59.344
What little I could make out.

611
00:31:59.368 --> 00:32:01.601
I mean. it's nine
kinds of crazy.

612
00:32:02.937 --> 00:32:04.537
But I found this too.

613
00:32:05.640 --> 00:32:07.285
Now.

614
00:32:07.309 --> 00:32:09.104
You're staying right
here till you tell me

615
00:32:09.128 --> 00:32:11.488
exactly what the
hell that means.

616
00:32:15.417 --> 00:32:16.749
[KNOCKING]

617
00:32:23.892 --> 00:32:26.121
Hi. uh. are you Joseph Welch?

618
00:32:26.145 --> 00:32:27.572
Yeah.

619
00:32:27.596 --> 00:32:29.741
JOSEPH: Yeah. He
was older. but that's him.

620
00:32:29.765 --> 00:32:31.709
Came by three or four days ago.

621
00:32:31.733 --> 00:32:33.310
Said he was a reporter.

622
00:32:33.334 --> 00:32:36.164
That's right. We're
working on a story together.

623
00:32:36.188 --> 00:32:39.868
Well. I don't know what kind
of story you're working on.

624
00:32:39.892 --> 00:32:41.402
The questions he asked me...

625
00:32:41.426 --> 00:32:43.838
About your late wife. Constance.

626
00:32:43.862 --> 00:32:46.507
He asked me where
she was buried.

627
00:32:46.531 --> 00:32:48.677
And where is that again?

628
00:32:48.701 --> 00:32:50.545
What. I gotta go
through this twice?

629
00:32:50.569 --> 00:32:52.097
It's fact-checking.

630
00:32:52.121 --> 00:32:54.020
If you don't mind.

631
00:32:55.524 --> 00:32:59.504
In a plot behind my old
place. over on Breckenridge.

632
00:32:59.528 --> 00:33:00.860
Why did you move?

633
00:33:02.731 --> 00:33:06.032
I'm not gonna live in the
house my children died.

634
00:33:08.920 --> 00:33:10.731
Mr. Welch. did you
ever marry again?

635
00:33:10.755 --> 00:33:11.750
No way.

636
00:33:11.774 --> 00:33:14.540
Constance. she was
the love of my life.

637
00:33:16.111 --> 00:33:18.089
Prettiest woman I ever known.

638
00:33:18.113 --> 00:33:19.980
So you had a happy marriage?

639
00:33:23.085 --> 00:33:24.750
Definitely.

640
00:33:26.989 --> 00:33:29.601
Well. that should do
it. Thanks for your time.

641
00:33:29.625 --> 00:33:31.624
[♪♪♪]

642
00:33:36.565 --> 00:33:38.197
[KEYS JINGLING]

643
00:33:40.268 --> 00:33:43.297
Mr. Welch. you ever
hear of a Woman in White?

644
00:33:43.321 --> 00:33:44.399
A what?

645
00:33:44.423 --> 00:33:45.933
A Woman in White.

646
00:33:45.957 --> 00:33:47.607
Or sometimes "Weeping Woman"?

647
00:33:48.343 --> 00:33:49.871
It's a ghost story.

648
00:33:49.895 --> 00:33:52.974
Well. heh. it's more of
a phenomenon. really.

649
00:33:52.998 --> 00:33:54.843
Um. they're spirits.

650
00:33:54.867 --> 00:33:57.345
They've been sighted
for hundreds of years.

651
00:33:57.369 --> 00:33:59.814
Dozens of places:
in Hawaii. Mexico.

652
00:33:59.838 --> 00:34:01.416
lately. in Arizona. Indiana.

653
00:34:01.440 --> 00:34:03.418
All these are different
women. you understand.

654
00:34:03.442 --> 00:34:05.420
but all share the same story.

655
00:34:05.444 --> 00:34:09.758
Boy. I don't care
much for nonsense.

656
00:34:09.782 --> 00:34:11.760
See. when they were alive.

657
00:34:11.784 --> 00:34:14.144
their husbands were
unfaithful to them.

658
00:34:14.953 --> 00:34:16.097
And these women.

659
00:34:16.121 --> 00:34:18.149
basically suffering
from temporary insanity.

660
00:34:18.173 --> 00:34:19.823
murdered their children.

661
00:34:21.009 --> 00:34:22.854
Then once they realized
what they had done.

662
00:34:22.878 --> 00:34:24.572
they took their own lives.

663
00:34:24.596 --> 00:34:26.607
So now their spirits are cursed.

664
00:34:26.631 --> 00:34:28.943
Walking back roads. waterways.

665
00:34:28.967 --> 00:34:30.945
And if they find
an unfaithful man.

666
00:34:30.969 --> 00:34:32.447
they kill him.

667
00:34:32.471 --> 00:34:34.791
And that man is
never seen again.

668
00:34:35.907 --> 00:34:38.519
You think...?

669
00:34:38.543 --> 00:34:42.123
You think that has something
to do with Constance.

670
00:34:42.147 --> 00:34:44.259
you smart-ass?

671
00:34:44.283 --> 00:34:45.715
You tell me.

672
00:34:49.120 --> 00:34:51.198
I mean. maybe...

673
00:34:51.222 --> 00:34:54.135
Maybe I made some mistakes.

674
00:34:54.159 --> 00:34:55.804
But no matter what I did.

675
00:34:55.828 --> 00:34:59.079
Constance. she never would
have killed her own children.

676
00:35:00.665 --> 00:35:03.311
Now. you get the
hell outta here.

677
00:35:03.335 --> 00:35:05.635
And you don't come back.

678
00:35:20.519 --> 00:35:22.429
I don't know how many
times I gotta tell you.

679
00:35:22.453 --> 00:35:24.916
it's my high school
locker combo.

680
00:35:24.940 --> 00:35:26.284
We gonna do this all night long?

681
00:35:26.308 --> 00:35:27.651
We just got a 911.

682
00:35:27.675 --> 00:35:29.355
Shots fired over
at Whiteford Road.

683
00:35:31.313 --> 00:35:33.490
You have to go to the bathroom?

684
00:35:33.514 --> 00:35:35.448
No. Good.

685
00:35:55.086 --> 00:35:56.519
Let's go.

686
00:36:00.291 --> 00:36:02.225
[♪♪♪]

687
00:36:18.209 --> 00:36:19.643
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

688
00:36:23.949 --> 00:36:25.777
[PHONE BEEPS]

689
00:36:25.801 --> 00:36:28.445
Fake 911 phone call.
Sammy? That's pretty illegal.

690
00:36:28.469 --> 00:36:31.165
You're welcome.
<i>Listen. we gotta talk.</i>

691
00:36:31.189 --> 00:36:34.051
Tell me about it. So the
husband was unfaithful.

692
00:36:34.075 --> 00:36:35.870
We are dealing with
a Woman in White.

693
00:36:35.894 --> 00:36:38.239
<i>She's buried behind her old
house. so Dad's next stop...</i>

694
00:36:38.263 --> 00:36:39.607
Sammy. would you shut up?

695
00:36:39.631 --> 00:36:41.409
<i>I can't figure out why
he hasn't destroyed</i>

696
00:36:41.433 --> 00:36:43.511
the corpse yet. <i>That's
what I'm telling you.</i>

697
00:36:43.535 --> 00:36:44.812
He's gone.

698
00:36:44.836 --> 00:36:46.681
Dad left Jericho. <i>What?</i>

699
00:36:46.705 --> 00:36:47.865
How do you know?

700
00:36:48.573 --> 00:36:49.684
I've got his journal.

701
00:36:49.708 --> 00:36:51.585
He doesn't go
anywhere without that.

702
00:36:51.609 --> 00:36:53.471
Yeah. well. he did
this time. What's it say?

703
00:36:53.495 --> 00:36:55.139
<i>Ah. that same old
ex-Marine crap.</i>

704
00:36:55.163 --> 00:36:56.507
to let us know where he's going.

705
00:36:56.531 --> 00:36:58.593
<i>Coordinates.</i> Where to?

706
00:36:58.617 --> 00:37:00.361
I'm not sure yet. <i>I
don't understand.</i>

707
00:37:00.385 --> 00:37:01.812
<i>I mean. what could
be so important</i>

708
00:37:01.836 --> 00:37:03.914
<i>that Dad would just skip
out in the middle of a job?</i>

709
00:37:03.938 --> 00:37:06.166
Dean. what the hell is going on?

710
00:37:06.190 --> 00:37:07.185
Whoa!

711
00:37:07.209 --> 00:37:09.008
[TIRES SCREECHING]

712
00:37:09.711 --> 00:37:11.077
Sam. Sam!

713
00:37:11.680 --> 00:37:13.679
[♪♪♪]

714
00:37:17.201 --> 00:37:18.518
Take me home.

715
00:37:24.309 --> 00:37:26.287
[ENGINE IDLING]

716
00:37:26.311 --> 00:37:27.576
Take me home.

717
00:37:29.114 --> 00:37:30.246
No.

718
00:37:31.683 --> 00:37:33.683
[♪♪♪]

719
00:38:10.822 --> 00:38:12.188
Don't do this.

720
00:38:15.060 --> 00:38:16.692
I can never go home.

721
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:21.130
You're scared to go home.

722
00:38:27.122 --> 00:38:28.366
[GRUNTS]

723
00:38:28.390 --> 00:38:30.335
Hold me.

724
00:38:30.359 --> 00:38:32.125
I'm so cold.

725
00:38:33.462 --> 00:38:35.106
But you can't kill me.

726
00:38:35.130 --> 00:38:36.841
I'm not unfaithful.

727
00:38:36.865 --> 00:38:39.215
I've never been.

728
00:38:40.685 --> 00:38:42.017
You will be.

729
00:38:44.489 --> 00:38:46.667
Just hold me.

730
00:38:46.691 --> 00:38:47.857
[GRUNTS]

731
00:39:02.808 --> 00:39:04.441
[SCREAMS]

732
00:39:09.781 --> 00:39:11.158
[SCREAMS]

733
00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:12.232
<i>[HEART POUNDING]</i>

734
00:39:13.184 --> 00:39:14.533
[SCREAMS]

735
00:39:24.546 --> 00:39:25.756
[ENGINE STARTS]

736
00:39:25.780 --> 00:39:27.564
I'm taking you home.

737
00:39:30.201 --> 00:39:31.267
DEAN: Sam!

738
00:39:41.712 --> 00:39:43.357
Sam? Here.

739
00:39:43.381 --> 00:39:44.447
You okay?

740
00:39:45.150 --> 00:39:46.127
I think.

741
00:39:46.151 --> 00:39:47.428
Can you move?

742
00:39:47.452 --> 00:39:49.018
Yeah. Help me.

743
00:39:53.158 --> 00:39:55.775
<i>[CHOIR SINGING]</i>

744
00:39:59.163 --> 00:40:01.043
There. There you go.

745
00:40:12.643 --> 00:40:13.643
[DEAN GRUNTS]

746
00:40:28.259 --> 00:40:30.259
[♪♪♪]

747
00:40:50.398 --> 00:40:52.782
BOTH: You've come
home to us. Mommy.

748
00:40:59.491 --> 00:41:00.656
[SCREAMING]

749
00:41:30.638 --> 00:41:32.821
So this is where
she drowned her kids.

750
00:41:34.475 --> 00:41:36.915
That's why she
could never go home.

751
00:41:37.528 --> 00:41:39.968
She was too scared to face 'em.

752
00:41:40.464 --> 00:41:42.609
You found her weak spot.

753
00:41:42.633 --> 00:41:43.710
Nice work. Sammy.

754
00:41:43.734 --> 00:41:45.014
[LAUGHS IN PAIN]

755
00:41:46.737 --> 00:41:48.482
Yeah. I wish I could
say the same for you.

756
00:41:48.506 --> 00:41:51.168
What were you thinking. shooting
Casper in the face. you freak?

757
00:41:51.192 --> 00:41:53.503
Hey. Saved your ass.

758
00:41:53.527 --> 00:41:55.072
[AC/DC'S "HIGHWAY
TO HELL" PLAYING]

759
00:41:55.096 --> 00:41:56.273
I'll tell you another thing.

760
00:41:56.297 --> 00:41:57.763
If you screwed up my car.

761
00:41:58.900 --> 00:42:00.210
I'll kill you.

762
00:42:00.234 --> 00:42:01.684
[CHUCKLES]

763
00:42:03.221 --> 00:42:07.335
<i>♪ Living easy. living free ♪</i>

764
00:42:07.359 --> 00:42:11.105
<i>♪ Season ticket
On a one-way ride ♪</i>

765
00:42:11.129 --> 00:42:12.940
<i>♪ Asking nothing... ♪</i>

766
00:42:12.964 --> 00:42:14.375
Okay. here's where Dad went.

767
00:42:14.399 --> 00:42:16.877
It's called Black
Water Ridge. Colorado.

768
00:42:16.901 --> 00:42:19.168
Sounds charming. How far?

769
00:42:20.138 --> 00:42:22.432
About 600 miles.

770
00:42:22.456 --> 00:42:24.534
If we shag ass. we
can make it by morning.

771
00:42:24.558 --> 00:42:26.937
[♪♪♪]

772
00:42:26.961 --> 00:42:28.327
Dean. I...

773
00:42:30.965 --> 00:42:32.008
You're not going.

774
00:42:32.032 --> 00:42:33.577
The interview's
in. like. 10 hours.

775
00:42:33.601 --> 00:42:34.761
I gotta be there.

776
00:42:39.474 --> 00:42:40.884
Yeah.

777
00:42:40.908 --> 00:42:43.442
Yeah. whatever.
I'll take you home.

778
00:42:46.781 --> 00:42:48.714
<i>♪ Highway to hell ♪</i>

779
00:42:50.251 --> 00:42:53.119
<i>♪ I'm on a highway to hell ♪</i>

780
00:43:04.265 --> 00:43:06.098
You'll call me if you find him?

781
00:43:08.235 --> 00:43:10.581
Maybe I can meet
up with you later. huh?

782
00:43:10.605 --> 00:43:11.987
Yeah. all right.

783
00:43:13.591 --> 00:43:15.068
[ENGINE STARTS]

784
00:43:15.092 --> 00:43:16.759
Sam.

785
00:43:20.281 --> 00:43:22.641
You know. we made a
hell of a team back there.

786
00:43:23.385 --> 00:43:25.285
Yeah.

787
00:43:43.171 --> 00:43:44.270
Jess?

788
00:43:45.956 --> 00:43:47.590
You home?

789
00:43:59.804 --> 00:44:02.354
